<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1273] rectify confusing &quot;Replication&quot; and &quot;Distribution&quot; links on solr admin screen</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1273</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Sine 1.0, the Solr Admin screen has had a &quot;Distribution&quot; link which points to &quot;distributiondump.jsp&quot; and displays stats according to data files created by the snappuller/snapinstaller scripts&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With the new java based replication, when a ReplicationHandler is enabled, we now have a &quot;Replication&quot; link on the admin page pointing to &quot;replication/index.jsp&quot; which displays stats/status for java based replication.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In at least one instance, these two different links confused a user...&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/Replication-In-1.4-to24356158.html#a24356158&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/Replication-In-1.4-to24356158.html#a24356158&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to rectify this confusion prior to releasing 1.4.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
